-- EXCLUSIVE-Schwab, Merrill, face SEC probe for anti-money laundering violations -sources 
-- 
-- Wed May 21, 2014 04:46PM EDT
-- None



NEW YORK, May 21 (Reuters) - U.S. regulators are investigating Charles Schwab Corp <SCHW.N> and Bank of America Corp's <BAC.N> Merrill Lynch brokerage over whether they are doing enough to police their clients' identities, two sources said.

The U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission is probing Charles Schwab and Merrill Lynch for violations of anti-money laundering rules that require the brokerages to know their customers, the sources said.